ymodify-desc:
Y-modify is a team which organized by engineer students.
We'll keep bringing somethin new to society with technology.
slider-ozone: Bring your favorite distro to the Intel Edison
slider-job: We are just doing our hobbies like jobs, but it's not jobs.
top-yamax:
YamaX is humanoid embedded Intel Edison.
It can perform voice recognition, speaking, remote control, etc...
top-flixa:
'Float, Flat, Flexible'
Gaming library for every platform
top-flixa-lang: Can be used in many programming languages
top-ozone:
Useful alternative OSs for Intel Edison.
Enjoy Intel Edison in familiar environment
yamax-desc:
'A Humanoid for Hobby'
For everyone who starts making humanoid from now on.
yamax-moving-desc:
Program for walking is directly written.
Beyond a lot of testing, we did make YamaX walk.
We took over months to do it.
yamax-voicecontrol-desc:
Intel Edison was embedded into YamaX.
Using embedded linux, it can perform voice recognition, speaking, remote control, etc..
yamax-structure-desc:
Almost things from frame of motor to control board are hand-maded.
This is robot
about-helping-desc:
Want to contribute to society? We feel like the same.
We'll help engineer students having overflowing technology being into society.
about-interaction-desc:
Maybe not crazy, but always be excited.
Every ideas won't be made when you're looking ground.
Starts with playful mind, either ends do.
about-creativity-desc:
'Complete' always goes away how you follow it.
It's awesome isn't it to make prototypes closer to complete thing?
member-nyanyan-desc:
This is Nyanyan, the CTO of Y-modify. I use this squirrel photo, as usual.
I make mainly YamaX hardware.
I am into rubik's cube lately.
I really, really want to get used to using command operation.
I will inprove light metals processing and increse the variation of that.
member-coorde-desc:
I'm coord.e.
I makes software of YamaX and Ozone OS.
I'm in public relations section after a fashion, so I also makes something involved with public relations like this webpage.
My maker life has started with PIC16F and assembly language, and I turned into a person of software side when I realized it.
I love Intel Edison and Arduino. 
Nowadays, I'm learning machine learning to make YamaX walk stably automatically.
